desc.eadoc:name: Legal Entity
desc.eadoc:note:
A legal entity able to transact business, typically registered with a body able to confer legal status such as a national business register.
In RDF terms, a legal entity is a sub class of dcterms:Agent and foaf:Agent.
In XML terms, this is equivalent to the UN/CEFACT term 'Business profile.'

desc.eadoc:name: Identifier
desc.eadoc:note: Any formally-issued identifier for a resource

desc.eadoc:name: Agent
desc.eadoc:note: A resource that acts or has the power to act.

desc.eadoc:name: Change
desc.eadoc:note: A record of a change in data

desc.eadoc:name: Licence
desc.eadoc:note: A place holder for a future licence class that is officially issued to a legal entity in order for them to carry out some activity or another. For example, a banking licence.
